Looking for a sea change to build your dream home then this prestige’s block is worth a look.

Description:
BAY AND ISLAND VIEWS
UNINTERRUPTED BAY VIEWS
This stunning 4 bedroom double storey home is located on the highest point in Pioneer Bay and overlooks parkland at the rear boundary where there is a private access gate from the house.
You will be totally amazed by the incredible Westernport and French Island view, not just a glimpse, this is a wide expansive view which cant be built out. The upstairs family zone includes the huge kitchen with stainless steel appliances and walk in pantry, dining area, large lounge/family room plus the master suite and a 4 th bedroom all set to share the full rear decks with bay views. Open up the stacker doors and bring that bay view and breezes in!
Downstairs features 2 very large bedrooms with full wall of mirrored robes, a family bathroom, internal access from the garage and a spacious laundry. Plenty of storage continues under the stairs and a full height double sliding cabinet to the laundry.
If you have been looking for a large family home with a view you cant go past this well maintained, park side home with it's 3 car garage with rear roller door for trailer or boat. Imagine breakfast on the deck and spending more time in the outdoors having friends and family over for bbqs as its large enough to host a large gathering.
The rear yard is spacious and currently features well laid out vegetable garden beds and fruit trees, a chook shed with run and lots of paving and a garden shed and water tank. It's move in ready for summer living.
Dont let this one pass you by!

ELEVATED GRAZING LAND CLOSE TO FERRY!

Central lane way provide convenient access to the two rear paddocks from Central yard.
Fences in excellent condition with ability to improve pasture an upside.
Top of the hill building envelope affords distant sea views sure to impress.
Best priced pasture on the island, do not miss this opportunity!
Contact Phil Bock on 0438 497 715 for further details or to arrange an inspection.

Description:
Final Stage of Eastern Shores - UNDER CONTRACT
Lot 18 Portview Avenue, 735m2
Eastern Shores Estate last and FINAL land release is underway with Titles expected early-mid 2018. The land enjoys views towards the sea and the woodland nature reserve next to the estate. Land sizes vary and the land whilst mostly flat has some elevated lots which will capture views. This is the final stage of land release in Grantville at present so get in early to secure your lot. Eastern Shores is located minutes stroll away from all the shops and services in Grantville which include a Post Office, Newsagency, Council Offices, Medical Centre, Ambulance station and Chemist. There are a number of Cafes and fast food outlets and a Bakery. Grantville is approx. 20 mins from San Remo, 30 mins from Wonthaggi and Cowes and approx. 35 mins from Cranbourne and Pakenham. There is an excellent new Early Childhood campus beside the popular Bass Valley Primary School and there are multiple Secondary School options in the locality. A V- Line Bus runs regularly to Melbourne and beyond into Gippsland. The township is growing rapidly but land is running out just as fast!
Deposit of $500 is due upon signing contracts with the balance of 10% deposit within 21 days. The balance will be due within 14 days of the Titles being issued by the Land Titles office.
Contact Liz Leahy for more information on 0487 022 099

Description:
MODERN LIVING – GRANTVILLE RISE ESTATE!!
This beautifully designed home is only 2 years old and is in immaculate condition.
Set within walking distance to shops, beach, and public transport facilities in a desirable location. Comprising of 3 bedrooms all with built-ins, master with ensuite, walk in robe, central bathroom. The home also offers formal lounge, light filled kitchen with updated appliances and open family living area. There are 3 split systems throughout the home, double glazed windows, floating floor boards, solar panels. Water tank for your garden that is easy- care low maintenance with rear yard also having carport access.
If you are looking for a new property with all the hard work done in the heart of Grantville this property is a must see.
If you are unable to attend a scheduled open please call for a private viewing.

Description:
Affordable home with bay views
Convenient, affordable and nicely placed, this is an ideal property for the astute investor. Situated in a quiet street and just minutes walk to the water, the property comprises three bedrooms with built-in robes, comfortable lounge room, adjoining meals area and a galley kitchen. It also includes a carport and good sized back yard. It is fenced for privacy and has elevated decks with views to the bay. Currently leased at $260pw, a healthy 5% return. This is the one that's not to be missed.

Local shops, ambulance depot and permanent doctor only a few kilometres and local primary school and kindergarten approx.. 6 mins. Good commute Pakenham and surrounds with dual lane highway.

Description:
BASS PARK
2705 Bass Highway, Bass represents on outstanding lifestyle opportunity in the high growth Bass Coast and Westernport Bay region. 106 Acres/42.96 Bass Park is ideally situated on the edge of the Bass Township with direct highway frontage.
Featuring a quality executive style brick veneer residence comprising 4 large bedrooms, 2 bathrooms and spacious living areas this quality home includes gas ducted heating, electric split cycle, wood heater plus all modern conveniences.
Excellent shedding for hay/machinery or stables plus stockyards compliments the property which is well fenced to 7 paddocks serviced by a central laneway. The highly productive property boasts a secure water supply via town water, bore and a reliable rainfall.
Bass Park is ideal for cattle/horses or most other agricultural interests while being close to pristine swimming/surf beaches and excellent boating & fishing.
San Remo 14km, Phillip Island 32km, Kilcunda 13km & Melbourne CBD 1 hour & 20 minutes.
Contact Carlo Taranto on 0418 368 739 from Elders Pakenham or Don Olden on 0417 805 312 or Jean OLoughlin on 0428 571 083 from Elders Korumburra & Leongatha
